                        "displayName": "Keith Pope",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "looks to me that it appends the path already?\n\n{code}\n$path = implode(PATH_SEPARATOR, $paths);\n        set_include_path($path . PATH_SEPARATOR . get_include_path());\n        return $this;\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mute",
                        "name": "mute",
                        "displayName": "Keith Pope",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-18T12:15:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-18T12:15:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34679",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Zend_Application prepends them as the assumption is that these are paths for your application and library code -- and as such should have preference over ZF code itself (for instance, consider if you have patched versions of ZF class files -- you can maintain them in your own version control and have them found while still using svn:externals or systemwide ZF install for the full library).\n\nIf you have a very specific include_path you need to use for performance reasons, it's often better to set this in your php.ini or vhost definition.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
